      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "959af24be13e798d",
      "text": "As the weeks continued, I had my own contributions to return to as well.  The axe handle emerging from the hickory tree, foraging, networked brains, the pattern language.  Over time, it felt like the contributions mattered.  Over time, my own lived experience was being more deeply felt.  Moments caught me off guard- when sharing Rose Poka's quote that \"None of us are alone\", my voice broke.  I paused.  I took a breath.  I was feeling the power of the collective.  I have been frequently writing about the collective, but now I was feeling it.  And as I felt it, I experienced it more completely. I could now see the rescuers on the shore, the faces of people in passing boats.  We could see, hear and feel each other.  Your words, thoughts, ideas, emotions matter to me."
